        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              My career seems to be at a standstill because I suck at / don't play office politics.<br /><br />I have been the technical lead on many projects but frequently my design decisions run up against someone else's prejudices, or who wants my resources who is better at office politics. I try to make my design decisions based on the product constraints and the business needs and keep everything data driven. When arguing a position I stick to the facts and  present the data and method the decision was reached. Unfortunately when presented with overwhelming facts, the typical response has been to trash me behind my back to senior management. I then have to justify myself to senior management where they have been told I'm an idiot and don't know what I'm talking about.<br /><br />So what am I doing wrong and how can I improve?

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
