              <div class="quotetitle">Skoop wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">How do things go when you have performance reviews?</div> I have never had a bad performance review. <br /><br />So I start at a company work on a couple of projects have some successes and I am given more responsibility and bigger projects. Eventually a lead in another group will question my approach, because they have the &quot;one true way&quot;. They raise a big stink up the org chart, while my boss usually supports me, they won't stick their neck out for me. Eventually it turns into analysis paralysis, I get frustrated and find employment elsewhere.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">You're at the wrong company.</div><br /><br />Thats what I thought, but it has happened a couple of times now at different companies.<br />Do I just work for bad companies?

              

              
              
            </div>
