              <div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I just work for bad companies?</div><br />Based on what you just replied, I'm thinking 'no'.<br /><br />There's something about your interactions with others that's putting people off.<br /><br />Edit:  Now, to be charitable, office politics, the subject of your post, is frequently about ambitions and jockeying for position.  I don't gather that that's what you're really asking about.  I get the sense that there's a more basic failure to grasp what makes for stable relations going on here.  Like being personable.  Being friendly.  Showing an interest in others.  Being something other than a robot geek.

              

              
              
