              <div class="quotetitle">Dragondazd wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">PoM tell us more about your relationships with your peers and your bosses. Tell us more about the sorts of politically-influenced activities you perform. Heck, remind us what you do.</div><br /><br />I'm an senior level embedded software engineer. I am usually the technical lead for software development responsible for architecting the software, managing the software schedule, and breaking up tasks to junior engineers and providing technical guidance. I collaborate with the project managers, marketing leads refining the product requirements. I also work with the technical leads of other disciplines such as the electrical team and mechanical team to define the system boundaries. I also work with QA coming up with test strategies and prioritizing and resolving issues.<br /><br />I would say I have worked well with all of these people, and many have given me recommendations and followed me to other jobs. While i do have an INTJ personality and don't schmooze much, I do interact often and well with others at a professional level.<br /><br />The instances where I had a knife thrown in my back were with other silos in the organization. One instance was one group was developing a cadillac product, our group was tasked with developing a cost sensitive product. The tech lead of the cadillac product wanted us to reuse the work they had done. I evaluated it and it was too costly to use because our product was cost sensitive. During that time the company was being acquired and re-orgs were happening, people were making political moves and unwilling to really stick their necks out.  While the PM and rest of team agreed with me but I was the one that had to defend the decision to senior management. After a month of meetings on the issue without resolve, I quit taking 2 coworkers with me to a new job.

              

              
              
