              PS. I don't tell other women I like their shoes just to make them like me. I tell them I like their shoes when I actually <span style="font-style: italic">like </span>their shoes. I say hi to the security guards when I'm leaving, because it's a pleasant ritual that makes <span style="font-style: italic">me </span>happy. I bring in leftover baked goods because I enjoy sharing things with my office mates.<br /><br />Don't start asking people about their kids just because you need to tick something off on your &quot;I'm a good coworker&quot; checklist. People will sense that you're being disingenuous and they will usually end up disliking you because of it. If you have a complimentary thought about someone, verbalize it (as long as it's work appropriate). If you need to kill time, shoot the breeze with someone. It makes work more pleasant for everyone.<br /><br />I don't say hi to the security guards for any other reason than I like saying hi to them. But I'll tell you that it will definitely not hurt to be friendly with them if I ever get locked out of my office.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
