              <div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Eventually it turns into analysis paralysis, I get frustrated and find employment elsewhere.</div><br />So, what in your analysis told you that it was time to leave? Everyone has friction at work. Having someone question what you do is natural, indeed, it is normal. Quitting when that happens is the wrong response. Respond in a proper manner and continue with your work.<br /><br />In other words, you have not really showed where your lack of politics screwed you. You have only shown where you have gotten pissy and left. This is not judgement, this is just how I see it. Can you think of an example where the lack of politics led to something more than someone questioning you so you would have to respond to them?

              

              
              
