              <div class="quotetitle">AndrewZ wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Sometimes a little homework helps a lot. I recommend this book to help with office relations, it is a classic:<br /><a href="http://www.amazon.com/How-Friends-Influence-People-Digital/dp/1451612591/ref=sr_1_3?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1362597864&amp;sr=8-3&amp;keywords=how+to+win+friends+and+influence+people" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">http://www.amazon.com/How-Friends-Influence-People-Digital/dp/1451612591/ref=sr_1_3?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1362597864&amp;sr=8-3&amp;keywords=how+to+win+friends+and+influence+people</a><br /><br />Getting to Yes is such a classic it should be required reading for EVERYONE:<br /><a href="http://www.amazon.com/Getting-Yes-Negotiating-Agreement-Without/dp/0143118757/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1362598110&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=getting+to+yes" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">http://www.amazon.com/Getting-Yes-Negotiating-Agreement-Without/dp/0143118757/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1362598110&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=getting+to+yes</a><br /><br />This one I haven't read yet but is highly recommended:<br /><a href="http://www.amazon.com/Secrets-Winning-Office-Politics-Influence/dp/0312332181" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">http://www.amazon.com/Secrets-Winning-Office-Politics-Influence/dp/0312332181</a><br /><br />This one is about dirty office politics that other people use, that you should know about&#058;<br /><a href="http://www.amazon.com/21-Dirty-Tricks-Work-Politics/dp/1841126578/ref=pd_sim_b_7" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">http://www.amazon.com/21-Dirty-Tricks-Work-Politics/dp/1841126578/ref=pd_sim_b_7</a></div><br /><br />I was going to suggest How to Win Friends and Getting to Yes also.  Spin Selling and Solution Selling are both very useful here... a little dated for field sales but the principles are still solid for interoffice political applications.<br /><br />I'd also say, in general, try to be happy and not take anything personally.  Smile a lot.  Pretty much everyone likes happy, smiley people.  Finally, take care of yourself.  Healthy people earn more, are promoted more and are hired more.

              

              
              
            </div>
