              I haven't found a good game theory book that applies game theory to how people really think. In order to apply the math, you have to understand what peoples' payoffs are, and that's really not very obvious at times.<br /><br />Ex. I had one woman be nasty to me when she was supposed to train me. Did not understand that in this particular instance, me learning her skill could be a direct threat to her livelihood. This is the 'obvious in hindsight' answer.

              

              
              
